result.execSummary:
All charges against Christine A Baukin in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christine A Baukin is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Hearing 1-28-22 filed by Court Reporter Amanda Chentnik

1:15 PM Court called 20CT124, 21CT58, 21TR496 and 22CM8. Prosecuting attorney Jordan Lippert appeared in court for the State of Wisconsin, Defendant Christine A Baukin appeared in court, Attorney Steven James Sarbacker appeared in court for Christine A Baukin. Scheduled for a global plea and sentencing.  ADA Lippert recited agreement.  1:19 PM in recess.  1:26 PM same cases recalled, appearances the same.  Rights and elements.  Defendant plead no contest to count 1 of 20CT124 and plead no contest to count 1 of 21CT58.  Court accepted the pleas and found defendant guilty of Count 1 of 20CT124 and Count 1 of 21CT58; judgments to be entered.  Counts 2 and 3 of 20CT124, count 2 of 21CT58, 22CM8 and 21TR496 all dismissed.  Sentencing statements. For count 1 of 20CT124 Court imposed and stayed 180 days jail with huber, ordered 24 months of probation with conditions of serving 18 days in the Columbia County Jail to begin 1-28-22 at 7 PM, Huber privileges subject to jail policies, no good time, pay $2122 in fines and costs, $65 blood draw reimbursement fee; 30 month revocation of license; 30 month ignition interlock, complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations; submit DNA sample; successfully complete OWI treatment court. For count 1 of 21CT58 Court ordered defendant to pay costs of $443 and submit a DNA sample.  4 days jail credit.  Adjourned at 1:51 PM.
